                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-23T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 23, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>692. My 690, December 22, 3 p.m. I have informed my British colleague of the
                    substance of my interview. He has had no intimation of the grounds assigned by
                    the authorities for their action.</p>
                <p>I am informed that one of the non-American letter writers is not even a member of
                    the mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
